---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SOURCES } from "@/lib/sources";
import { highlightYaml, highlightMarkdown } from "@/lib/shiki";
import type { PageSEO } from "@/lib/types";
import { version } from "../../package.json";

const sources = Object.values(SOURCES);

const sampleYaml = `---
title: "29 USC § 1022 - Summary plan description"
title_number: 29
title_name: "LABOR"
section_number: "1022"
section_name: "Summary plan description"
chapter_number: 18
chapter_name: "EMPLOYEE RETIREMENT INCOME SECURITY PROGRAM"
positive_law: false
currency: "119-73"
last_updated: "2025-12-08"
format_version: "1.1.0"
generator: "lexbuild@${version}"
source_credit: "(Pub. L. 93–406, title I, § 102, Sept. 2, 1974, 88 Stat. 841; Pub. L. 104–191, title I, § 101(c)(2), Aug. 21, 1996, 110 Stat. 1951; Pub. L. 104–204, title VI, § 603(b)(3)(C), Sept. 26, 1996, 110 Stat. 2938; Pub. L. 105–34, title XV, § 1503(b), Aug. 5, 1997, 111 Stat. 1061; Pub. L. 111–3, title III, § 311(b)(1)(B), Feb. 4, 2009, 123 Stat. 67.)"
---`;

const samplePreviewFields = [
  { label: "Identifier", value: "/us/usc/t29/s1022" },
  { label: "Currency", value: "119-73" },
  { label: "Positive Law", value: "No" },
  { label: "Updated", value: "2025-12-08" },
  { label: "Chapter", value: "18 — Employee Retirement Income Security Program" },
];

const sampleMarkdown = `# § 1022. Summary plan description

**(a)** A summary plan description of any employee benefit plan shall be furnished to participants and beneficiaries as provided in section 1024(b) of this title. The summary plan description shall include the information described in subsection (b), shall be written in a manner calculated to be understood by the average plan participant, and shall be sufficiently accurate and comprehensive to reasonably apprise such participants and beneficiaries of their rights and obligations under the plan. A summary of any material modification in the terms of the plan and any change in the information required under subsection (b) shall be written in a manner calculated to be understood by the average plan participant and shall be furnished in accordance with section 1024(b)(1) of this title.

**(b)** The summary plan description shall contain the following information: The name and type of administration of the plan; in the case of a group health plan (as defined in section 1191b(a)(1) of this title), whether a health insurance issuer (as defined in section 1191b(b)(2) of this title) is responsible for the financing or administration (including payment of claims) of the plan and (if so) the name and address of such issuer; the name and address of the person designated as agent for the service of legal process, if such person is not the administrator; the name and address of the administrator; names, titles, and addresses of any trustee or trustees (if they are persons different from the administrator); a description of the relevant provisions of any applicable collective bargaining agreement; the plan's requirements respecting eligibility for participation and benefits; a description of the provisions providing for nonforfeitable pension benefits; circumstances which may result in disqualification, ineligibility, or denial or loss of benefits; the source of financing of the plan and the identity of any organization through which benefits are provided; the date of the end of the plan year and whether the records of the plan are kept on a calendar, policy, or fiscal year basis; the procedures to be followed in presenting claims for benefits under the plan including the office at the Department of Labor through which participants and beneficiaries may seek assistance or information regarding their rights under this chapter and the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 with respect to health benefits that are offered through a group health plan (as defined in section 1191b(a)(1) of this title), the remedies available under the plan for the redress of claims which are denied in whole or in part (including procedures required under section 1133 of this title), and if the employer so elects for purposes of complying with section 1181(f)(3)(B)(i) of this title, the model notice applicable to the State in which the participants and beneficiaries reside.

---

**Source Credit**: (Pub. L. 93–406, title I, § 102, Sept. 2, 1974, 88 Stat. 841; Pub. L. 104–191, title I, § 101(c)(2), Aug. 21, 1996, 110 Stat. 1951; Pub. L. 104–204, title VI, § 603(b)(3)(C), Sept. 26, 1996, 110 Stat. 2938; Pub. L. 105–34, title XV, § 1503(b), Aug. 5, 1997, 111 Stat. 1061; Pub. L. 111–3, title III, § 311(b)(1)(B), Feb. 4, 2009, 123 Stat. 67.)

## Editorial Notes

### References in Text

This chapter, referred to in subsec. (b), was in the original "this Act", meaning , known as the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974. Titles I, III, and IV of such Act are classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under  and Tables.

The Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996, referred to in subsec. (b), is , , . For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title of 1996 Amendment note set out under , The Public Health and Welfare, and Tables.

### Amendments

2009—Subsec. (b).  substituted ", the remedies" for "and the remedies" and inserted ", and if the employer so elects for purposes of complying with , the model notice applicable to the State in which the participants and beneficiaries reside" before the period at end.

1997—, substituted "Summary plan description" for "Plan description and summary plan description" in section catchline.

Subsec. (a). , struck out "(1)" after subsec. designation and struck out par. (2) which read as follows: "A plan description (containing the information required by subsection (b)) of any employee benefit plan shall be prepared on forms prescribed by the Secretary, and shall be filed with the Secretary as required by . Any material modification in the terms of the plan and any change in the information described in subsection (b) shall be filed in accordance with ."

Subsec. (b). , substituted "The summary plan description shall contain" for "The plan description and summary plan description shall contain".

1996—Subsec. (b).  made technical amendment to references in original act which appear in text as references to .

inserted "in the case of a group health plan (as defined in ), whether a health insurance issuer (as defined in ) is responsible for the financing or administration (including payment of claims) of the plan and (if so) the name and address of such issuer;" after "type of administration of the plan;" and "including the office at the Department of Labor through which participants and beneficiaries may seek assistance or information regarding their rights under this chapter and the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 with respect to health benefits that are offered through a group health plan (as defined in )" after "presenting claims for benefits under the plan".

## Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries

### Effective Date of 2009 Amendment

Amendment by  effective , and applicable to child health assistance and medical assistance provided on or after that date, with certain exceptions, see , set out as an Effective Date note under , The Public Health and Welfare.

### Effective Date of 1996 Amendments

Amendment by  applicable with respect to group health plans for plan years beginning on or after , see  set out as a note under .

Amendment by  applicable with respect to group health plans for plan years beginning after , except as otherwise provided, see , set out as an Effective Date note under .

### Regulations

Secretary authorized, effective , to promulgate regulations wherever provisions of this subchapter call for the promulgation of regulations, see .`;

let highlightedYaml: string;
let highlightedMarkdown: string;
try {
  highlightedYaml = await highlightYaml(sampleYaml);
  highlightedMarkdown = await highlightMarkdown(sampleMarkdown);
} catch {
  highlightedYaml = `<pre><code>${sampleYaml}</code></pre>`;
  highlightedMarkdown = `<pre><code>${sampleMarkdown}</code></pre>`;
}

const siteUrl = import.meta.env.SITE_URL ?? "https://lexbuild.dev";
const seo: PageSEO = {
  title: "LexBuild — U.S. Law as Structured Markdown",
  rawTitle: true,
  description:
    "U.S. federal law and regulations as structured Markdown. Browse, search, copy, and download the U.S. Code and Code of Federal Regulations for LLMs, RAG pipelines, and semantic search.",
  canonicalUrl: siteUrl,
  ogType: "website",
  ogImage: `${siteUrl}/og-image.png`,
  jsonLd: {
    "@type": "WebSite",
    name: "LexBuild",
    url: siteUrl,
    description: "U.S. federal law and regulations as structured Markdown for LLMs, RAG, and semantic search.",
  },
};

Astro.response.headers.set("Cache-Control", "public, s-maxage=3600, stale-while-revalidate=86400");
---

<BaseLayout seo={seo}>
  <section class="bg-surface border-border-base bg-grid-pattern border-b">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-6 py-12 text-center sm:py-16">
      <div class="text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-400 inline-flex h-14 w-14 items-center justify-center">
        <svg
          class="h-11 w-11"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="1.75"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path
            d="m12.83 2.18a2 2 0 0 0-1.66 0L2.6 6.08a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.83l8.58 3.91a2 2 0 0 0 1.66 0l8.58-3.9a1 1 0 0 0 0-1.83Z">
          </path><path d="m22 17.65-9.17 4.16a2 2 0 0 1-1.66 0L2 17.65"></path><path
            d="m22 12.65-9.17 4.16a2 2 0 0 1-1.66 0L2 12.65">
          </path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h1
        class="font-display text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-100 mb-2 text-[clamp(2.5rem,5vw,3.5rem)] leading-tight font-semibold tracking-tight">
        LexBuild
      </h1>
      <p class="font-display text-slate-blue-700 dark:text-slate-blue-300 mb-6 text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">
        U.S. Legal Text as Structured Markdown
      </p>
      <p class="text-ink-muted mx-auto mb-7 max-w-[796px] text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
        An open-source CLI toolchain and searchable web resource for U.S. federal and state legal texts. Convert
        official source data into structured Markdown built for LLMs, agentic workflows, RAG pipelines, and semantic
        search systems.
      </p>
      <div
        class="text-slate-blue-700 dark:text-slate-blue-400 mb-8 flex items-center justify-center gap-2 text-[14px] font-medium">
        <span class="font-bold whitespace-nowrap">1.05M+ Documents</span>
        <div class="bg-slate-blue-500 dark:bg-slate-blue-600 h-3.5 w-px"></div>
        <span class="font-bold whitespace-nowrap">Updated Daily</span>
        <div class="bg-slate-blue-500 dark:bg-slate-blue-600 h-3.5 w-px"></div>

        <span class="font-bold whitespace-nowrap">MIT Open Source</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <a
          href="#quickstart"
          class="bg-slate-blue-700 border-slate-blue-800 hover:bg-slate-blue-800 hover:border-slate-blue-800 inline-flex cursor-pointer items-center gap-2 rounded-sm border px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition-all duration-150">
          CLI Quick Start
          <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/chris-c-thomas/LexBuild"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-slate-blue-900 border-slate-blue-300 hover:border-slate-blue-500 hover:bg-slate-blue-50 dark:bg-slate-blue-800 dark:text-slate-blue-200 dark:border-slate-blue-700 dark:hover:border-slate-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-slate-blue-800 inline-flex cursor-pointer items-center gap-2 rounded-sm border bg-white px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold transition-all duration-150">
          <svg class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
            <path
              d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.31 3.435 9.795 8.205 11.385.6.105.825-.255.825-.57 0-.285-.015-1.23-.015-2.235-3.015.555-3.795-.735-4.035-1.41-.135-.345-.72-1.41-1.23-1.695-.42-.225-1.02-.78-.015-.795.945-.015 1.62.87 1.845 1.23 1.08 1.815 2.805 1.305 3.495.99.105-.78.42-1.305.765-1.605-2.67-.3-5.46-1.335-5.46-5.925 0-1.305.465-2.385 1.23-3.225-.12-.3-.54-1.53.12-3.18 0 0 1.005-.315 3.3 1.23.96-.27 1.98-.405 3-.405s2.04.135 3 .405c2.295-1.56 3.3-1.23 3.3-1.23.66 1.65.24 2.88.12 3.18.765.84 1.23 1.905 1.23 3.225 0 4.605-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.925.435.375.81 1.095.81 2.22 0 1.605-.015 2.895-.015 3.3 0 .315.225.69.825.57A12.02 12.02 0 0024 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z">
            </path>
          </svg>
          View on GitHub
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="quickstart" class="border-border-base border-b py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <div class="mb-6">
        <h2 class="font-display text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-200 mb-1 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
          CLI Quick Start
        </h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted text-[15px]">
          No complex configuration required. Additional CLI options are available.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-slate-blue-50 border-slate-blue-200 dark:bg-card dark:border-border rounded-sm border p-5 sm:p-6">
        <div class="mb-3 flex flex-col gap-1.5">
          <span
            class="text-slate-blue-700 border-slate-blue-300 bg-slate-blue-100 dark:text-slate-blue-300 dark:border-slate-blue-600 dark:bg-slate-blue-900 self-start rounded-sm border px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-[11px] font-medium tracking-wider uppercase">
            USC
          </span>
          <span class="text-[15px] font-normal">
            Download all 54 Titles of the U.S. Code directly from the source <a
              href="https://uscode.house.gov/download/download.shtml"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-slate-blue-700 hover:text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-400 dark:hover:text-slate-blue-200 font-medium">
              XML
            </a> provided by the <a
              href="https://uscode.house.gov/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-slate-blue-700 hover:text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-400 dark:hover:text-slate-blue-200 font-medium">
              OLRC
            </a> and convert into per-section Markdown files.
          </span>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-slate-blue-950 overflow-x-auto rounded-sm p-4 font-mono text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[#d4dce4]">
          <div>
            <span class="text-slate-blue-400">$</span>
            <span class="text-white">npx @lexbuild/cli download-usc</span>
            <span class="text-putty-300">--all</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-slate-blue-400">$</span>
            <span class="text-white">npx @lexbuild/cli convert-usc</span>
            <span class="text-putty-300">--all</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 mb-1 flex flex-col gap-1.5">
          <span class="text-[15px] font-normal">
            Download and convert a single title, such as <a
              href="/usc/title-29"
              class="text-slate-blue-700 hover:text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-400 dark:hover:text-slate-blue-200 font-medium">
              Title 29
            </a>, which includes <a
              href="/usc/title-29/chapter-18/section-1022"
              class="text-slate-blue-700 hover:text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-400 dark:hover:text-slate-blue-200 font-medium">
              Section 1022
            </a> as shown in the <a
              href="#sample-output"
              class="text-slate-blue-700 hover:text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-400 dark:hover:text-slate-blue-200 font-medium">
              sample output
            </a> below.
          </span>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-slate-blue-950 overflow-x-auto rounded-sm p-4 font-mono text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[#d4dce4]">
          <div>
            <span class="text-slate-blue-400">$</span>
            <span class="text-white">npx @lexbuild/cli download-usc</span>
            <span class="text-putty-300">--titles 29</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-slate-blue-400">$</span>
            <span class="text-white">npx @lexbuild/cli convert-usc</span>
            <span class="text-putty-300">--titles 29 --include-notes</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-5 flex justify-center">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/chris-c-thomas/LexBuild/blob/main/docs/reference/cli-reference.md"
          class="text-slate-blue-800 border-slate-blue-300 hover:border-slate-blue-500 hover:bg-slate-blue-50 dark:bg-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-200 dark:border-slate-blue-700 dark:hover:border-slate-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-slate-blue-800 inline-flex cursor-pointer items-center gap-2 rounded-sm border bg-white px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold transition-all duration-150">
          <svg
            class="h-4 w-4"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round">
            <polyline points="4 17 10 11 4 5"></polyline>
            <line x1="12" y1="19" x2="20" y2="19"></line>
          </svg>
          Full CLI Docs
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="sources" class="bg-slate-blue-50 dark:bg-slate-blue-950/50 border-border-base border-b py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
      <div class="mb-6">
        <h2 class="font-display text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-200 mb-1 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
          Browse Sources
        </h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted text-[15px]">
          Explore U.S. federal law and regulations as structured Markdown, no CLI required. Browse, copy, or download
          entire titles, chapters, parts, or sections straight from the browser.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {
          sources.map((source) => (
            <a
              href={source.basePath}
              class="group border-border bg-card hover:border-slate-blue-400 dark:hover:border-slate-blue-600 flex flex-col rounded-sm border p-6 transition-[border-color,box-shadow] hover:shadow-md">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="text-slate-blue-700 dark:text-slate-blue-400 text-xs font-bold tracking-wider">
                  {source.shortName}
                </span>
                <span class="bg-slate-blue-200 dark:bg-slate-blue-800 h-px flex-1" />
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-slate-blue-700 dark:group-hover:text-slate-blue-300 mt-3 font-sans text-xl font-semibold transition-colors">
                {source.name}
              </h2>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">{source.description}</p>
              <div class="text-slate-blue-700 dark:text-slate-blue-400 mt-auto flex items-center justify-evenly pt-4 text-xs font-medium">
                {source.id === "usc" ? (
                  <>
                    <span class="text-center">{source.titleCount} titles</span>
                    <span class="bg-slate-blue-300 dark:bg-slate-blue-700 mx-1 h-3 w-px shrink-0" />
                    <span class="text-center">{source.chapterCount.toLocaleString()} chapters</span>
                    <span class="bg-slate-blue-300 dark:bg-slate-blue-700 mx-1 h-3 w-px shrink-0" />
                    <span class="text-center">{source.sectionCount.toLocaleString()} sections</span>
                  </>
                ) : source.id === "ecfr" ? (
                  <>
                    <span class="text-center">{source.titleCount} titles</span>
                    <span class="bg-slate-blue-300 dark:bg-slate-blue-700 mx-1 h-3 w-px shrink-0" />
                    <span class="text-center">{source.partCount?.toLocaleString()} parts</span>
                    <span class="bg-slate-blue-300 dark:bg-slate-blue-700 mx-1 h-3 w-px shrink-0" />
                    <span class="text-center">{source.sectionCount.toLocaleString()} sections</span>
                  </>
                ) : (
                  <>
                    <span class="text-center">Published daily since 2000</span>
                    <span class="bg-slate-blue-300 dark:bg-slate-blue-700 mx-1 h-3 w-px shrink-0" />
                    <span class="text-center">~770k documents</span>
                  </>
                )}
                <span class="text-slate-blue-400 dark:text-slate-blue-300 ml-1 shrink-0 text-sm transition-transform duration-200 group-hover:translate-x-1 group-hover:scale-125">
                  &rarr;
                </span>
              </div>
            </a>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="pipeline" class="border-border-base border-b py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
      <div class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-display text-slate-blue-900 dark:text-slate-blue-200 mb-1 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
          How It Works
        </h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted text-[15px]">
          The CLI toolchain converts source data to structured Markdown. The web resource and data API make it
          browsable, searchable, and programmatically accessible.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- CLI wrapper — the outermost container reflecting the dependency graph -->
      <div class="pipeline-cli">
        <div class="pipeline-cli-header">
          <div class="pipeline-cli-icon">
            <svg
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              class="h-5 w-5">
              <polyline points="4 17 10 11 4 5"></polyline><line x1="12" y1="19" x2="20" y2="19"></line>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="pipeline-cli-name">@lexbuild/cli</div>
            <div class="pipeline-cli-role">Orchestrates the full pipeline</div>
          </div>
          <div class="pipeline-cli-steps">
            <span class="pipeline-cli-step">Download</span>
            <span class="pipeline-cli-step-arrow">→</span>
            <span class="pipeline-cli-step">Parse</span>
            <span class="pipeline-cli-step-arrow">→</span>
            <span class="pipeline-cli-step">Convert</span>
            <span class="pipeline-cli-step-arrow">→</span>
            <span class="pipeline-cli-step">Write</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pipeline-cli-body">
          <!-- CLI depends on core -->
          <div class="pipeline-depends pipeline-depends-cli" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              class="pipeline-depends-arrow">
              <path d="M12 5v14"></path><path d="m19 12-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
            <span class="pipeline-depends-label">CLI depends on</span>
            <svg
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              class="pipeline-depends-arrow">
              <path d="M12 5v14"></path><path d="m19 12-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="pipeline-flow">
            <!-- Source XML column -->
            <div class="pipeline-stage">
              <div class="pipeline-stage-label">Source</div>
              <div class="pipeline-source-stack">
                <div class="pipeline-source pipeline-source-usc">
                  <div class="pipeline-source-icon">
                    <svg
                      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                      fill="none"
                      stroke="currentColor"
                      stroke-width="1.75"
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      class="h-4 w-4">
                      <path d="m16 16 2 2 4-4"></path><path
                        d="M21 10V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l2-1.14">
                      </path><path d="m7.5 4.27 9 5.15"></path><polyline points="3.29 7 12 12 20.71 7"></polyline><line
                        x1="12"
                        y1="22"
                        x2="12"
                        y2="12">
                      </line>
                    </svg>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <div class="pipeline-source-title">USLM 1.0 XML</div>
                    <div class="pipeline-source-meta">
                      <a class="pipeline-source-url hover:underline" href="https://uscode.house.gov">uscode.house.gov</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="pipeline-source pipeline-source-ecfr">
                  <div class="pipeline-source-icon">
                    <svg
                      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                      fill="none"
